title: SPIDER-MAN: No Way Home - WTF is Happening in this Movie, EXPLAINED | Dr. Strange Kang Breakdown
author: ScreenCrush
comment: I'm glad I'm not the only one who watched that trailer and was like, "Why is Dr. Strange acting like a fratboy dumbass?"
i like how he always gives credit to the ppl who said something useful.
No one is going to mention why Strange is hanging out in an ice room? Sounds like something a demon would do, if he could....
Ryan is a humble man. Giving credit when the same people don’t show him the same respect. RESPECT!
description:
Spider-Man: No Way Home shows Peter and Doctor Strange breaking open the multiverse in a big way, merging the MCU with villains like Doctor Octopus, Electro, and the Green Goblin.

But how exactly did this happen? What was the spell that Strange cast that made the multiverse split? What do the multiple trains mean? We break down all of the hidden meanings and exactly what this means for the multiverse going forward.

Also, Mephisto.
